basics.name: Mohammed Nabil Al-Qalisi
basics.label: Software  Developer
basics.summary: I am a software developer extraordinaire, always on the lookout for innovative and exciting solutions to complex problems. I am proficient in a variety of programming languages and frameworks, and I love nothing more than tackling new challenges, both independently and as part of a team. Whether I'm debugging code or brainstorming new ideas, I'm always looking for ways to grow and expand my skillset. So if you're looking for a talented and passionate software developer, look no further!

work.summary: I provide expertise in software development and related services to clients on a project basis as a software development consultant. I work independently, offering a variety of services including coding, software design, testing, and debugging. Additionally, I provide guidance on best practices, project management, and other related areas to help clients achieve success. As a software freelancer, I have experience managing multiple projects simultaneously and am adept at managing my time and resources effectively to meet project deadlines.
highlights: Successfully managed multiple projects concurrently, ensuring timely delivery and high-quality output.
Provided expert guidance on software development best practices, project management, and related areas to clients.
Demonstrated proficiency in a range of programming languages, frameworks, and tools to deliver high-quality software solutions.
Maintained excellent communication skills and responsiveness to client feedback, resulting in long-term client relationships and repeat business.
Continuously pursued professional development opportunities to stay current with emerging trends and technologies in the software development field.

work.summary: I work as a pedagog in a government agency where I develop and implement educational programs and initiatives that promote environmental awareness and sustainable practices. My job involves designing and delivering engaging educational materials and activities for different audiences, including school groups, community organizations, and the general public. I collaborate with other departments to integrate environmental education into their programs and policies, and conduct research to stay up-to-date with emerging trends and best practices in environmental education. Additionally, I advocate for policies that support sustainable practices to help protect the environment and ensure a better future for our planet.
